Go to Appearance > Menus > At the top, Screen Options > CSS Classes Check it. Then in the new menu item CSS, add new_menu_item to the field.

Then paste in the customizer > custom css

.new_menu_item .ts-item-icon:after{
	content: "";
	width: 10px;
	height: 10px;
	border-radius: 100px;
	background: #9CD6E0;
	position: absolute;
	top: 5px;
	right: 3px;
}

.new_menu_item{
	position: relative;
}

.new_menu_item .ts-term-icon:after{
	content: "";
	width: 10px;
	height: 10px;
	border-radius: 100px;
	background: #9CD6E0;
	position: absolute;
	top: 5px;
	left: 24px;
}
